data.text:
DescriptionEU US Summit, Gothenburg 2001.jpg

English: The first summit meeting of the European Union with the new American administration was held in Gothenburg (Sweden) in the framework of the European Council. The President of the European Commission, Romano Prodi, and the Swedish Prime Minister and President-in-Office of the Council, Göran Persson, met the President of the United States, George W. Bush and other high representatives of the two parties, in particular the Secretary-General of the Council of the EU and High Representative for the Common Foreign and Security Policy, Javier Solana. Group photo1st row, from left to right:Romano Prodi, President of the EC; Tarja Halonen, President of Finland; George W. Bush, President of the United States; Göran Persson, Swedish Prime Minister; Jacques Chirac, President of the French Republic;Guy Verhofstadt, Belgian Prime Minister; Poul Nyrup Rasmussen, Danish Prime Minister; Wolfgang Schüssel, Austrian Federal Chancellor 2nd row:António Guterres, Portuguese Prime Minister; Gerhard Schröder, German Federal Chancellor; Silvio Berlusconi, Italian Prime Minister; Paavo Tapio Lipponen, Finnish Prime Minister; Bertie Ahern, Irish Prime Minister; Tony Blair, British Prime Minister
